Title: Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 - Trailer 3 (Official)
Comment:
Just saw the film and may I say I LOVED IT! Iam incredibly honored and happy to say that I really loved this film, and that it is another Marvel hit. Let me start off by saying that the film was extremely fun and unique. The colors, visuals, and scenery was beaut IFUL and pleasing to lay your eyes on. The planets, space, lifeforms, everything was really well done, and you can tell they paid a lot od attention to detail. The action was superb and had an exciting atmosphere that created a very fun and crazy tone. The style of action and fighting really brought another mostly fresh take and door opening to the MCU. A lot of exolosions, guns, missles, blasters, space fights, spaceships, jeckpacks and more was included in the film, and man was it awesome! But to me where the film really shines is in the characters. I did not expect the film to be so emotional and depressing, and how hard hitting certain moments and scenes were. A lot of times, and one big moment in the film where a character reveals something about another characters mother, the WHOLE AUDITORIUM GASPS and you felt the emotion in the air. People were crying and sobbing, and you hear and see everyone in a upset state of mind. Yes the movie was extremely fun but where it lies is how well most of the characters were developed. GREAT JOB TO THE MAIN CAST! CHRIS PRATT AS STARTLORD, BRADLEY COOPER AS ROCKET, ZOE SALDANA AS GAMORA, DAVE BAUTISTA AS DRAX, VIN DIESEL AS GROOT, KURT RUSSELL AS EGO, MICHAEL FRICKIN ROOKER AS YONDU AND MANTIS (I cannot remember the actresses name).YOU ALL DID GREAT! Every character within the film fleshes out, and has their own time to shine and show their developement. Throughout the film, you bond with the Guardians and really see their emotional and human side, which leaves the audience in tears and saddness. Starlord was incredible and really added a human element to the film, and shows why people love him so much. You cannot hate him because he is too good, and you really see him develope even more.Drax provided great humor to the movie, but also grew as a character as well. Gamora was great and she began to develope and show a soft side, and her emotional side really shows. Baby Groot was adorable, and this made him seem so innocent and pure which gave the film more emotion. Mantua was good although she came in a little late. Who was good, but I CANNOT speak to much on him because of spoilers. But to me, the two that really stood out and got the most development were Yondu and Rocket. I cannot explain how much emotion and humanity that have the film. Every scene that were in that had your eyes watery and has you depressed because you really got to see the side of themselves you would never have thought you would see. I LOVED THEM IN THE FILM! THE whole audience would gasps, cry, and aww the two, especially Rocket, because they had you gripped and thinking about them constantly. And oh man they have some of the best, and saddest scenes in the movie and imo comic book movie history. Besides the positives the film does have things holding it back. Nebula to me was overused and over exaggerated.Even though she has a dark past, she felt a little bit to angry at times and her acting seemed forced. The first and third act were incredible, but the middle was a little choppy with its storytelling and plot, even though the STORY itself is great. But all in all, I FRICKIN LOVED GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY VOLUME 2! I recommend everyone to go check this movie out, if you weren't going to already for some rwasonüòï. If your a comic book fan or movie fan, this movie will blow your hearts away and satisfy you. A great film that anyone can love. Great Job to the cast of Guardians of the Galaxy Volume 2 for the great amrketing, promoting, interviews, merchandise, hype, and overall great movie. Thank you Marvel for giving out another hit!
